StremeBase 0.1 JavaDoc

Stremebase is a simple experimental zero-configuration embeddable multi-model database backend (storage engine) written from scratch to support the high level Java 8 Streams API.

See: Description

Packages 
Package Description
com.stremebase.base  
com.stremebase.map  

Stremebase is a simple experimental zero-configuration embeddable multi-model database backend (storage engine) written from scratch to support the high level Java 8 Streams API.

Stremebase is meant for graph algorithm research, domain-driven design, agile development and rapid prototyping. Start with Stremebase, choose the final DBMS according to you information model, not the other way round.
